Our health tracking system is centred around several recurring real-world concepts that shape both user interaction and architectural design. These concepts represent meaningful entities in the problem domain rather than technical implementation details. They inform the system’s structure and will guide later design and development decisions.

User
Real-World Concept
•	A person engaging with the system to monitor and improve their health behaviours
Representation within our System
•	Unique user account
•	Login credentials
•	Profile information
•	Role (standard user, admin, etc)
Link to our User stories
•	User Story 1: “As a user, I want to navigate the app easily and enter data quickly so that tracking my health feels simple and not overwhelming”.
•	User Story 5: “As Olivia, I want to compare my progress with friends using a ranking system so that I stay motivated to train”.
The User concept is central to the system. All other domain entities are associated with a user
Profile
Real-World Concept
A structured personal identity containing relevant background information
Representation in the system
•	Age, weight, height 
•	Preferences
•	Health goals 
•	Activity settings
Links to user journeys
When a user first registers, they create a profile that informs personalised tracking and feedback. The profile influences progress calculations 




Health Metric 
Real-World Concept
A measurable indicator of health or behaviour
Representation in the System 
•	Metric type
•	Value
•	Timestamp
•	Associated user
Links to user stories
•	User Story 4: “As Leonard, I want to track my fitness progress over time so that I can monitor improvement and stay motivated.”
•	User Story 2: “As Kieran, I want to log my daily food intake so that I can build better eating habits and improve my health.”
Health metrics form the primary data stored in the system and enable progress tracking
Goal
Real World Concept
A target outcome a user aims to achieve
Representation in the system
•	Target value
•	Timeframe
•	Progress status
Link to user journeys
When users set goals, the system compares logged metrics against these targets and provides feedback or ranking updates
Goals provide direction and motivation









Progress
Real-World concept
Change over time toward a desired outcome
Representation in the system 
•	Trend analysis 
•	Daily summaries 
•	Historical comparisons
Link to user stories
User Story 4: “As Leonard, I want to track my fitness progress over time so that I can monitor improvement and stay motivated”
Progress is derived from multiple health metrics and displayed through visualisations and summaries
Friendship
Real-World Concept
A social connection between users enabling shared comparison and motivation
Representation in the system
•	Friend Request 
•	Approved connection
•	Shared ranking visibility
Link to user stories
User Story 5: “As Olivia, I want to compare my progress with friends using a ranking system so that I stay motivated to train”
Friendship enables the ranking feature and increases engagement

Ranking
Real-World Concept
A comparative ordering of users based on progress or performance
Representation in the System
•	Calculated score 
•	Leaderboard position
•	Comparison metrics
Link to user journey
After progress updates, the system recalculates rankings and updates the leaderboard, which then reinforces motivation

Feedback & Notifications
Real-World Concept
Information and notification provided to users to encourage behavioural change
Representation in the system
•	Daily summaries 
•	Notifications
•	Visual progress indicators
Link to user stories
•	Users receive feedback after logging food or exercise
•	Notifications reinforce habit formation
